\begin_layout Standard
In summary, the main insights from these experiments are the following:
 (i) the results for the two datasets are similar.
 So, we show only the results obtained while querying using the claims section
 for CLEF-IP 2011; (ii) in general, query expansion is always useful for
 short queries (i.e.
 title, abstract, and claims), whereas for the whole patent application
 (including the description section), query expansion may hurt the performance
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Itoh2004,Magdy2011"

\end_inset

; (iii) MMRQE is more effective for complex queries (claims).
 Thus, diversity is may be not that important for short queries; (iv) the
 best section to use for querying is the claims.
 This is certainly due to the fact that the claims contain more information
 with more precise terms; (v) the best sources for expansion are the abstract
 and claims sections.
 It is interesting to notice that the description is not a good source for
 expansion, since it may contain more technical and general terms, which
 may hurt performance.
 Since the title section is not that rich regarding terms, the title is
 not useful as source of expansion; (vi) Rocchio is better in retrieving
 patent since it gives best performance for PRES in general, while MMRQE
 is better for ranking since it gives better performance for MAP.
 Finally, we also implemented the approach proposed in 
